05697nam a22010095i 9783035621662DE-B159720230103011142.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230103t20222023sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830356216627 a10.1515/97830356216622doi  a(DE-B1597)545480  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 4aTH4818.P3bB85 2023 7aARC0090002bisacsh04a693.922300aBuilding with Paper :bArchitecture and Construction /ced. by Ulrich Knaack, Samuel Schabel, Rebecca Bach. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2022] 4c©2023  a1 online resource (200 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- t1 PAPER IN ARCHITECTURE -- t2 MATERIAL -- t3 SEMI-FINISHED PRODUCTS AND COMPONENTS -- t4 BUILDING CONSTRUCTION -- t5 LOAD-BEARING STRUCTURE, FIRE PROTECTION, BUILDING PHYSICS -- t6 CASE STUDIES -- t7 OUTLOOK -- t8 FACTS AND FIGURES FOR ENGINEERS -- tAPPENDIX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas natürliche Material Papier und Pappe ist derzeit Gegenstand der Forschung und Erprobung in der Baupraxis. Es ist kostengünstig herstellbar, besteht aus nachwachsendem Rohstoff und ist gut rezyklierbar. Der Schwerpunkt der Verwendung liegt dabei auf der temporären Nutzung, etwa in Übergangsbauten für Schulen, Notunterkünfte oder „Microhomes". Richtig vor Nässe und Feuer geschützt, erweist sich das Material als sehr haltbar. Und der architektonische Anspruch kommt dabei keineswegs zu kurz, wie Beispiele von Pritzker-Preisträger Shigeru Ban zeigen: die Grundschule Chengdu, die Paper Concert Hall in Aquila oder die Cardboard Cathedral in Christchurch waren jeweils ein Zeichen der Hoffnung nach verheerenden Erdbeben. Die Einführung erklärt die Grundlagen des Bauens mit Papier und zeigt spannende Anwendungen.  aPaper and cardboard as sustainable building materials are currently the subject of research and testing. They can be produced inexpensively, are made from renewable raw materials and are completely recyclable. The focus of their application is on temporary uses, such as for transitional schools, emergency shelters or "microhomes". Properly protected from moisture and fire, the material proves to be durable. Design and aesthetic qualities are by no means neglected, as case studies by Pritzker Prize winner Shigeru Ban demonstrate: the Chengdu Elementary School, the Paper Concert Hall in Aquila or the Cardboard Cathedral in Christchurch all provided a sign of hope after devastating earthquakes. This introduction explains the technology of building with cardboard and paper and shows a wide range of examples.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aHouse construction. 0aPaperboard. 4aAusstellungsdesign. 4aBaustoff. 4aKarton. 4aNotunterkünfte. 4aPapier. 4aPappe. 4aRezyklierbarkeit. 7aARCHITECTURE / Methods & Materials.2bisacsh  aPaper.  aWikkelhouse.  acardboard.  acorrugated board.  amicrohome.  arenewable building material.  asustainability.  atiny house.1 aBach, Rebecca, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKnaack, Ulrich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchabel, Samuel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z978311076682008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2022z9783110992793oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG0 